					<p> This Day (Lagos) - July 25, 2006 | Juliana Taiwo - Abuja | The Japanese Government has offered to sponsor the training of Nigerian teachers in special science subjects at the African Education Institute, Kenya. Japanese Ambassador to Nigeria, Mr. Akio Tanaka disclosed this during a courtesy call on the Minister of Education, Mrs. Obiageli Ezekwesili. He said the Ministry would select the teachers to benefit from the training that promises to be a continuous exercise, adding that it was different from the activities of the Japanese International Co-operation Agency (JICA) in Nigeria, which include the construction of toilets and bore holes in some schools in three states of the Federation.</p>
