<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Zambia-Science-in-Country-s-Development-Plan-for-First-Time" title="Zambia: Science in Country's Development Plan for First Time" alt="link">Zambia: Science in Country's Development Plan for First Time</a></h2>

	
					<p> 
Talent Ngandwe | Lusaka - July 26, 2006 | The Zambian government has published the first national development plan to include a chapter on science and technology. Science ministry officials welcome the government's recognition that science has a role to play in national development, but have expressed concern that the plan allocates too little money to the sector.The 2006-2010 plan unveiled on 24 July is the country's fifth, but its first since 1990. It identifies priorities such as training researchers, improving working conditions to keep scientific talent in Zambia, and providing tax breaks to encourage the private sector to invest in research and development. </p>
