					<p> The Monitor (Kampala) - August 1, 2006 | Elias Biryabarema, Kampala - Suruma allocated Shs8b to support research in fruit processing, banana production and malaria research this year. On June 6, while inducting his newly appointed ministers, President Y.K. Museveni said the promotion of research and scientific innovation would be one of his priorities in the next five years. He was emphatic in noting that Uganda stands no chance of propelling itself to greater levels of economic development if it does not tame its excessive consumption and acquire matching technological capacity to create its own wealth. That objective, which is a critical component of the government's broader vision of modernising the economy was given anchorage by the Finance Minister Dr Ezra Suruma when he allocated a total of Shs8 billion to support reaserch in fruit juice processing and banana production in this financial year. </p>
