<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/WARDA-Strengthens-Biotech-Capacity-of-National-Partners-in-Africa" title="WARDA Strengthens Biotech Capacity of National Partners in Africa " alt="link">WARDA Strengthens Biotech Capacity of National Partners in Africa </a></h2>

	
					<p> 27 June 2006 | The Benin-based Africa Rice Center (WARDA) is offering a capacity building program in state-of-the-art molecular biology tools for sub-Saharan African national agricultural research programs, in response to &quot;strong demand&quot; from member countries. A &quot;major thrust&quot; of the new program is a three-year project being funded by USAID to address the &quot;intractable problem&quot; of rice yellow mottle virus (RYMV). The WARDA-USAID RYMV project will help research staff from the national programs in Burkina Faso, Guinea, Mali, and The Gambia use marker-assisted selection techniques to speed the process of developing RYMV-resistant rice varieties.</p>
