					<p> WWF calls suitable candidates to apply for the position of Transfly Ecoregion Coordinator in Papua New Guinea. The incumbent will ensure the strategic linkage and effectiveness of WWF ecoregional activities in the Transfly Ecoregion, feeding into WWF's wider forests and freshwater programmes.  The Coordinator is responsible for the development of and supporting the implementation of Ecoregion conservation initiatives in the TransFly Ecoregion in Papua New Guinea, fundraising for and ensure effective management of the Transfly projects in PNG and coordinating with the WWF Papua TransFly team to ensure the co-development and integration of the Ecoregional conservation programme on both sides of the border.  </p>
