<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Nile-Basin-Research-Programme-call-for-10-guest-researchers-applications-before-31-July-2006" title="Nile Basin  Research Programme: call for 10 guest researchers (applications before 31 July 2006)" alt="link">Nile Basin  Research Programme: call for 10 guest researchers (applications before 31 July 2006)</a></h2>

	
					<p> Nile Basin Research Programme (NBRP) of the Unversity of Bergen (Norway)  is a multidisciplinary programme for Nile Basin related research and education aimed to give researchers from academic institutions in the ten Nile Basin countries an opportunity to work together in research groups in a multidisciplinary, fertile academic environment in collaboration with researchers from outside the Nile Basin. It is supported by the governments of the region as a research component of the Nile Basin Initiative (NBI) and aims at supporting the general objectives of Applied Training Project under NBI's Shared Vision Programme. Each researcher is supposed to stay at the University of Bergen for a five month period.  Research themes will vary and have been indicated in the <a href="http://nile.uib.no/docs/NBRPProgPlanFinalOK.pdf" target="_blank">programme document</a>.</p>
